---
description: Security and trading safety rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Security is a blocking quality gate.

Requirements:

- Never commit, print or expose secrets.
- Never use default credentials in production-like environments.
- Validate all external inputs.
- Enforce authentication and authorization on the backend.
- Apply least privilege.
- Avoid SQL injection.
- Avoid command injection.
- Avoid unsafe deserialization.
- Protect browser flows against XSS and CSRF.
- Do not log tokens, passwords, credentials or sensitive payloads.
- Pin dependencies and container images.
- Generate and validate SBOMs.
- Use signed artifacts when supported.
- Prefer non-root containers.
- Drop unnecessary capabilities.
- Use read-only filesystems where practical.
- Separate paper, sandbox and live credentials.
- Never allow UI state to authorize financial actions.
- Never allow direct broker access without authorization.
- Fail closed for critical compliance and execution boundaries.

Any change involving:

- credentials,
- broker execution,
- authorization,
- human approvals,
- tenant data,
- restricted lists,
- payments,
- live trading

requires explicit security review.
